    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "data": {
            "children": [
              {
                "data": {
                  "value": "The variation of information is defined as VI(X,Y) = H(X|Y) + H(Y|X). If X is the ground-truth segmentation, then H(X|Y) can be interpreted as the amount of under-segmentation and H(X|Y) as the amount of over-segmentation. In other words, a perfect over-segmentation will have H(X|Y)=0 and a perfect under-segmentation will have H(Y|X)=0."
                },
                "type": "Words"
              }
            ]
          },
          "type": "Paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 0,
      "title": null
    },
